@5    = ~Cormlle naa tanya tel'raa - your heart is that of a lion.~
@6    = ~There is an old greeting: Elen sila lumenn omentilmo. It can be loosely translated as 'A star shall shine on the hour of our meeting.'~
@7    = ~Mellonamin, if you wish to converse in Elvish to practice what lessons you have received in Candlekeep, let us do so, but I do not see any value in me uttering a few words in my tongue solely for amusing you.~
@8    = ~Cuamin linduva yassen megrille - my bow shall sing with your sword.~
